			<div id="about-usc">
				<p>NUANSA Cultural Productions started as a humble initiative by a group of Indonesian students from National University of Singapore (NUS) in 2008, with the aim to showcasing the rich and diverse Indonesian culture to the Singapore community.</p>
				<p>Since its inception, NUANSA has significantly grown from strength to strength in terms of production quality as well as audience outreach. As a production group, we are proud to receive continued support from the Embassy of The Republic of Indonesia in Singapore.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="vision-missionc">
				<br>
				<h4 class="content-title">VISION</h4><hr class="belowtitle">
				<p>A cultural production showcasing and preserving the rich and diverse Indonesian culture to the Indonesian and Singaporean community.</p>
				<br>
				<h4 class="content-title">MISSION</h4><hr class="belowtitle">
				<p>Through the productions of NUANSA, we aim to achieve the following objectives:<ul>
					<li>Preserving and promoting culture from different parts of Indonesia.</li>
					<li>Reaching out to the Singapore community, including but not limited to Singaporeans, Indonesians in Singapore and foreigners.</li>
					<li>Nurturing members to achieve their fullest potential.</li>
					<li>Providing platform to express their creativity and interest.</li>
				</ul></p>
			</div>
